description:
Máquina Zero (Eng.: Machine Zero) is an international anthology of comics that mixes works of veteran artists and new talents of the sequential art.

The project began with a group of friends assembling comics from different parts of Brazil and the World. São Paulo, Argentina, Minas Gerais, Italy, Bahia, France, Pernambuco, Serbia, Rio de Janeiro, United States… the prove that comics doesn’t have frontiers.
name: Máquina Zero

description:
The beautiful and hard-hitting work of Giancarlo Berardi (writer) and Ivo Milazzo (artist) was originally published in 1976 in Il Giornalino and traveled all Europe.

With a surprisingly accurate vision of the situation that horrified the world and still remains unpunished, the Italian duo created one of the most authentic and original Brazilian of the worldwide comic books.

Inexplicably, Tiki has never been published in Brazil before. Almost forty years later its original publication, Tiki – O Menino Guerreiro (Eng.: Tiki – The Young Warrior) finally gets a Brazilian edition.
name: Tiki, O Menino Guerreiro

description:
The Bunker - Your Future Ends...Now.

A unique blend of reverse time travel, impending doom, and who's responsible for the end of the world, and what you would do if you knew you were responsible, or will have been responsible?

A creator-owned series and print edition of the digital series of the same name, and for the first time in full color. The double-sized debut issue collects the five digital chapters that were released online, via Hoarse and Buggy Productions. From the second print issue onwards The Bunker has been turned into an ongoing print series that, according to creator/writer J.H. Fialkov, could run for 40, 50, 60 issues.

Collected Editions

  • The Bunker Volume 1 (#1-4)
  • Oni Press Starter Pack 2016 (#1)
  • The Bunker Volume 2 (#5-9)
  • The Bunker Volume 3 (#10-?)
name: The Bunker
